Twelve clubs from across Africa will play 30 total regular-season games. After a Super 6 playoff, Kigali, Rwanda will host the BAL Final Four & BAL Final. NIKE and Jordan Brand will be the exclusive outfitter of the BAL, scheduled to tip off March 2020.

The Basketball Africa League (BAL) announces host cities, season structure and outfitter ahead of inaugural season. Cities include Cairo, Egypt; Dakar, Senegal; Lagos, Nigeria; Luanda, Angola; Rabat, Morocco; and either Monastir or Tunis, Tunisia.
